    {
      "id": "30284f70_2092143d",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/init/CpsNotificationSubscriptionModelLoader.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 59,
      "message": "I was thinking on the scenario below:\n\n1- All model loaders successfully loaded models (assuming).\n\n2- ModelLoaderCoordinatorEnd with Order(999) be called. Then, it will check isMaster flag true to release the lock. \n\n3- Then, it will go AbstractModelLoader.java -> checkIfThisInstanceIsMaster\n\n4- Then, ModelLoaderCoordinatorLock -> cpsCommonLocks.tryLock(\"modelLoaderLock\")\n\nDo you think that tryLock function will return true, to make ModelLoaderCoordinatorEnd master and set isMaster to true?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 8063,
        "name": "Halil Cakal",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "halil.cakal@est.tech",
        "username": "halil.cakal"
      },
      "updated": "2025-10-24 14:45:07.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "54d8e70d_888f2f47",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "da4f4f5e_46311903",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/init/InventoryModelLoader.java",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 73,
      "message": "the master restarting due to an error could cause issues I suppose. But that is an edgecase not the normal scenario.This would be the case for ANY hazelcast lock so I hope that Hazelcast has a way of release locks in case of an instance crash...",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2025-10-28 10:27:14.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5ff24da6_a1c10a6c",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "6e55554e_a3e47cd4",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/init/CpsNotificationSubscriptionModelLoader.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 59,
      "message": "Locks are held be an CPS instance not by a class/object or thread ie the 'master' instance HAS the lock ie. any time a class tries to acquire the lock it realizes it already has it... \nThe lock gets released AFTER all model loaders are finished by the last 'model loader': ModelLoaderCoordinatorEnd",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2025-10-28 10:27:14.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "30284f70_2092143d",
      "unresolved": true
